美国计算机协会 (ACM) 图灵奖通常被称为“计算机界的诺贝尔奖”，颁发给对计算领域具有持久重要性的重大贡献者。

The Association for Computing Machinery (ACM) Turing Award, often referred to as the "Nobel Prize of Computing," is given for major contributions of lasting importance to computing.

超过一半的图灵奖获得者在其职业生涯的某个阶段都曾获得美国国家科学基金会的资助。美国国家科学基金会很荣幸能够支持这些获奖者的工作，他们的工作极大地推动了科学和社会的发展。

More than half of Turing awardees have been funded by the U.S. National Science Foundation at some point in their careers. NSF is proud to support the work of these awardees, whose work has greatly advanced science and society.

图灵奖以英国数学家艾伦·M·图灵的名字命名，他阐明了计算的数学基础和局限性。自 1966 年以来，ACM 每年都会向为计算做出持久重大技术成就的个人颁发奖项。

The Turing Award is named for Alan M. Turing, the British mathematician who articulated the mathematical foundation and limits of computing. Since 1966, the ACM has been awarded annually to individuals who have contributed lasting and major technical accomplishments to computing.

获奖者名单如下，获得 NSF 资助的获奖者旁边标有星号 (*)。

The awardees are listed below with an asterisk (*) next to those who have received NSF funding.

*2023 年——阿维·威格德森 (Avi Wigderson)

*2023 — Avi Wigderson

首次获得 NSF 奖的年份： 2000 年。

Year of first NSF award: 2000.

图灵奖颁奖词： 表彰其对计算理论的奠基性贡献，包括重塑我们对随机性在计算和数学中的作用的理解，以及他在理论计算机科学领域数十年的智力领导地位。

Turing Award citation: For foundational contributions to the theory of computation, including reshaping our understanding of the role of randomness in computation and mathematics, and for his decades of intellectual leadership in theoretical computer science.

2009 年——查尔斯·P·（查克）·萨克

2009 — Charles P. (Chuck) Thacker

图灵奖颁奖词： 由于其对第一台现代个人计算机（施乐帕洛阿尔托研究中心的 Alto）的开创性设计和实现，以及在局域网（包括以太网）、多处理器工作站、侦听缓存一致性协议和平板个人计算机方面的开创性发明和贡献。

Turing Award citation: For the pioneering design and realization of the first modern personal computer — the Alto at Xerox PARC — and seminal inventions and contributions to local area networks (including the Ethernet), multiprocessor workstations, snooping cache coherence protocols and tablet personal computers.

图灵奖颁奖词： 因其三项独特而完整的成就：

Turing Award citation: For three distinct and complete achievements:

  • LCF，即斯科特可计算函数逻辑的机械化，可能是第一个基于理论但又实用的机器辅助证明构建工具。
  • LCF, the mechanization of Scott's Logic of Computable Functions, probably the first theoretically based yet practical tool for machine assisted proof construction.
  • ML，第一种包含多态类型推断和类型安全异常处理机制的语言。 
  • ML, the first language to include polymorphic type inference together with a type-safe exception-handling mechanism. 
  • CCS，一种并发性的一般理论。此外，他还制定并大力推进了完全抽象，即操作语义和指称语义之间关系的研究。
  • CCS, a general theory of concurrency. In addition, he formulated and strongly advanced full abstraction, the study of the relationship between operational and denotational semantics.

图灵奖引文： 威尔克斯教授最为人所知的是 EDSAC 的建造者和设计者，这是第一台具有内部存储程序的计算机。EDSAC 于 1949 年建成，使用水银延迟线存储器。他还因与惠勒和吉尔于 1951 年合著《电子数字计算机程序准备》一书而闻名，该书有效地引入了程序库。

Turing Award citation: Professor Wilkes is best known as the builder and designer of the EDSAC, the first computer with an internally stored program. Built in 1949, the EDSAC used a mercury delay line memory. He is also known as the author, with Wheeler and Gill, of a volume on "Preparation of Programs for Electronic Digital Computers" in 1951, in which program libraries were effectively introduced.
